rComments: She is easily the worst instructor so far in my life. I wish I could rate her even lower. She is not ready to be the instructor of a key course at the UofT. She doesn't respect students. Hopefully, she reads these comments to improve herself or stop teaching. Amanda: Lecture vs. Reading slides. Feedback on papers is essential for learning.

She is the worst. She told us that her questions were not memory-based, but rather application style problem-solving. She then proceeded to ask us the most nit-picky memorization questions I've ever seen on a test. Basically, if you have a photographic memory you'll do just fine in this class, everyone else is screwed. She is also really boring.

The course overall was pretty dense, but she delivered it in a somewhat interesting manner. You can tell she had a deep interest in the course material since I think she is a clinical psychologist. There was so much to memorize for the tests, and every little detail mattered!
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class']
